          <p><strong>SkyWatcher SynScan:</strong> SkyWatcher's controller for AZ-GTi, Star Adventurer, EQ mounts. Database: 42,000+ objects. Features: WiFi connectivity (control via smartphone), good tracking accuracy, firmware updates via USB. More technical interface than Celestron but powerful features. Excellent value on mid-range mounts.</p>

          <p><strong>Meade AutoStar / AudioStar:</strong> Meade's hand controllers for LX and ETX series. Database: 30,000+ objects, AudioStar adds voice descriptions. Features: Guided tours, Astronomer Inside audio, intuitive menus. Quality tracking and alignment. Less popular than Celestron/SkyWatcher currently but older Meade scopes still excellent performers.</p>

          <p><strong>Orion StarSeeker:</strong> Orion's GoTo controller for StarSeeker series and SkyView Pro mounts. Database: 42,000+ objects. Features: simplified operation for beginners, good alignment wizard. Generally good value but less refined than premium systems. Suitable for casual users prioritizing ease over advanced features.</p>
